dc_description_s: Relief shown by hachures. Inset: Liberia. Prime meridian: Washington, D.C. No. 35 in Colton, G.W. "Atlas of the world", v.2., 1856. Shows northwestern Africa including Morocco, Algeria, Sahara, Senegal and Guinea. 1 map: col.; 37 x 30 cm This map is in the public domain. Please attribute access and use of this digitized map to the Stephen S. Clark Library, University of Michigan Library.
